# MDX Content & Case Studies

## Directory Structure
- MDX files: `content/case-studies/[slug].mdx`
- Images: `public/images/[slug]/[image-name].png`

## Frontmatter Requirements
Each case study must include:
- `title`: string
- `category`: string (e.g., "UX Strategy", "Design Ops")
- `description`: string (one-liner for cards)
- `role`: string
- `duration`: string
- `team`: string
- `scope`: string
- `focus`: string (optional)
- `logo`: string (optional) — decorative header logo path under `public/`, e.g. `/images/slug/logo.svg`
- `image`: string (optional) — path under `public/`, e.g. `/images/slug/hero.png`
- `imageWidth` / `imageHeight`: numbers (optional) — intrinsic pixel size of `image` for correct home preview aspect; defaults match shared hero exports (1606×1008) if omitted

## MDX Components
- **Figure**: Use the `<Figure />` component for all images.
  - Props: `src`, `alt`, `caption`.
  - Example: `<Figure src="/images/slug/img.png" alt="Alt text" caption="Description" />`

## Content Structure
- Use semantic headings (h2, h3).
- Maintain a consistent narrative: Overview -> The Challenge -> Research/Process -> Solution -> Results -> Key Learnings.
